reviews.review_text: Great Show Not big break outs yet but a great Shakedown>Jack Straw.It probably helps that I was about 30 feet from Phil looking across at Jerry.
7-9-89 Great show and another wonderful remaster cy Charlie Miller.

WOW I could write a book about just getting to and from this show.

Haven't heard it in 21 years.

Would love to get a copy if anyone canb help me out.

Tommy
ts1012@aol.com

solid solid 89 show here, what a great setlist such an even mix of 80s tunes and earlier tunes, all the 80s songs are great i love getting to hear em all in 1 show

great show overall

Summer 89 what a hey day The last tent city tour, where most venues you could just camp in the parking lots, how convenient.

This show is up there with shoreline, alpine, and cal expo which are all the cream of the summer. The tour itself; they were consistently  playing SOooooo elevated and tight it was incredible to see live.

And if you were in the right spot, down low in the impact zone, it was the mothers milk of sound quality.

Peace
3 times is a charm bobby there's a you tube video (part 1 and 2 ) of this show. i can relate bobby. great sound wishit  had more phil
What a show! The Throwing Stones>NFA is some of the hottest playing that I have ever heard!  Jerry takes it to a whole other level.  Goosebumps, man!

wow its was pouring rain this show.had a seat behind the stage,was almost alone with my friend back there,still sounded great and we had an incredible time. listening to the brokedown now and remembering it being as nice as i remember,been a long time since i've heard it.

Another fine show in the swamps of joisey Actually the rain was the next night.  Was lucky enough to be under the mezzanine myself & stayed relatively dry lol. This night stands out for many reasons inc healy fuckin w john scher's intro of the boys into a SMOKIN Shakedown. The eve seemed to just get better w each song.   First set cooks & sets the stage perfectly for set 2 that among too many highlights to lost includes what may be the finest china>rider I've seen at a show i was at.   Hot hot night in the meadowlands.   So kick back crank up the volume & enjpy this damn fine show.   Truly a standout in a summer tour filled w fine shows

Giant show at Giants Stadium Just got back from 6 months in the Middle East and heard they were playing at Giants in a few days, which is 45 minutes away by car. Got a ticket in the lot. Mid field, middle deck. WOW what a super-charged show it was. 80,000 phreaks getting down. One of the most epic shows I saw as EVERYONE was digging it! From first row to nosebleed seats the place was-a-rockin'

Memorable shows Great Great times.Just graduated high school and did the tour. Remember having our tents right in the lot. They had tanker trucks brought in for fresh water. Also remember just as Shakedown began swarms of people were jumping down onto the floor. It looked like a waterfall of people.Great memories.

Su89 Giants Stadium N1 Shakedown Street opener! I love these summer shows, every damn last one of them, really. Some playful lyrical flubs early on, but it works itself out. Otherwise, I really dig the song selection of the first set, from start to finishing Bird Song. No Garcia ballad post-drumz. Just some good ole' rock and roll from the Grateful Dead. Brokedown Palace encores.
